[
  {
    "text": "Hi, I'm Ben Bodner from the Display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "and Color Technologies team at Apple.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=2"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this video, I'll explain the capabilities, use cases, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=4"
  },
  {
    "text": "and APIs of the new Reference Mode on iPad Pro.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=8"
  },
  {
    "text": "To help you understand Reference Mode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=12"
  },
  {
    "text": "I should first describe what a reference display is.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=13"
  },
  {
    "text": "Many displays intentionally manipulate the color, contrast, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=16"
  },
  {
    "text": "and sharpness of images.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=19"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, TVs usually have different modes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=22"
  },
  {
    "text": "that each target some unique aesthetic appearance, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=24"
  },
  {
    "text": "and mobile devices often adapt to ambient lighting.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=27"
  },
  {
    "text": "While these sorts of features may be desirable ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=30"
  },
  {
    "text": "in most situations, they can be problematic ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=32"
  },
  {
    "text": "for content creators who usually want to know ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=34"
  },
  {
    "text": "exactly how their display is rendering images.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=38"
  },
  {
    "text": "For that reason, reference displays render color ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=41"
  },
  {
    "text": "precisely to the specifications for a media format.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=43"
  },
  {
    "text": "That means if you have different reference displays, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=48"
  },
  {
    "text": "they will all render the same content consistently.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=49"
  },
  {
    "text": "This consistency gives content creators the ability ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=53"
  },
  {
    "text": "to use multiple displays with the confidence that their work ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=55"
  },
  {
    "text": "will look the same on all of them, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=57"
  },
  {
    "text": "assuming they are viewed in the appropriate lighting environment ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=59"
  },
  {
    "text": "for their media format.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=62"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now that we have an understanding ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=64"
  },
  {
    "text": "of reference displays, let's get into the details ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=65"
  },
  {
    "text": "of Reference Mode on iPad.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=67"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, I'll explain when and how to use Reference Mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=70"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, I'll cover the specific capabilities of Reference Mode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=74"
  },
  {
    "text": "including which media formats are supported.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=77"
  },
  {
    "text": "And last, I'll give a rundown of the APIs ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=80"
  },
  {
    "text": "associated with Reference Mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=82"
  },
  {
    "text": "So, when is it appropriate to use Reference Mode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=85"
  },
  {
    "text": "and how do we enable it? ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=88"
  },
  {
    "text": "Reference Mode enables or enhances a variety ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=91"
  },
  {
    "text": "of content creation workflows.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=93"
  },
  {
    "text": "It adds support for color-critical tasks ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=96"
  },
  {
    "text": "that require a reference display, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=97"
  },
  {
    "text": "which historically have not been possible on mobile devices.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=99"
  },
  {
    "text": "This includes color grading, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=102"
  },
  {
    "text": "along with review and approval of graded content.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=104"
  },
  {
    "text": "It also brings color accuracy to mobile video editing ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=107"
  },
  {
    "text": "and compositing apps, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=109"
  },
  {
    "text": "improving the experience for users ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=111"
  },
  {
    "text": "who typically would not have access to a reference display.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=112"
  },
  {
    "text": "Finally, Reference Mode supports both Metal ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=116"
  },
  {
    "text": "and AVFoundation-based color rendering, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=119"
  },
  {
    "text": "so apps serving these workflows can use either of them.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=121"
  },
  {
    "text": "Reference Mode is similar to the reference display presets ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=125"
  },
  {
    "text": "already available on some macOS systems ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=128"
  },
  {
    "text": "but with an important difference.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=130"
  },
  {
    "text": "On macOS, multiple preset modes are available ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=132"
  },
  {
    "text": "that each deliver reference color rendering ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=135"
  },
  {
    "text": "for different formats.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=137"
  },
  {
    "text": "On iPad, Reference Mode is just one setting ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=139"
  },
  {
    "text": "that is either turned on or off.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "That means you can get reference color rendering ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=145"
  },
  {
    "text": "for multiple formats without the need to change settings.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=146"
  },
  {
    "text": "This mode can only be accessed through the iPad settings ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=150"
  },
  {
    "text": "by a user and cannot be programmatically enabled ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=153"
  },
  {
    "text": "or disabled by an app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=155"
  },
  {
    "text": "Reference Mode is supported ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=159"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the 12.9-inch fifth-generation iPad Pro.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=160"
  },
  {
    "text": "It can be used with an iPad as a standalone device, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=164"
  },
  {
    "text": "but it also brings new capability to Sidecar, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=167"
  },
  {
    "text": "a feature that allows an iPad to be used ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=169"
  },
  {
    "text": "as a secondary monitor for a macOS device.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=171"
  },
  {
    "text": "Previously, Sidecar did not support EDR.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=174"
  },
  {
    "text": "But now, if Reference Mode is enabled on an iPad ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=177"
  },
  {
    "text": "used as a Sidecar display, it will support EDR in addition ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=179"
  },
  {
    "text": "to enabling reference color rendering for supported formats.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=183"
  },
  {
    "text": "This new functionality also requires an Apple silicon Mac ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=187"
  },
  {
    "text": "with macOS Ventura to be used as the host ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=189"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the Sidecar display.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=192"
  },
  {
    "text": "Enabling Reference Mode manipulates several other items ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=195"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the Settings menu.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=197"
  },
  {
    "text": "To achieve consistent color rendering, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=200"
  },
  {
    "text": "the brightness slider is locked and dynamic display features ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=201"
  },
  {
    "text": "are turned off.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=204"
  },
  {
    "text": "This includes disabling and locking True Tone ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "and Night Shift, along with the Auto-Brightness feature.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=207"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now that I've explained when and how ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=211"
  },
  {
    "text": "to enable Reference Mode, let's take a closer look ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=212"
  },
  {
    "text": "at what it means to run the reference color, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=215"
  },
  {
    "text": "along with the specific capabilities of Reference Mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=217"
  },
  {
    "text": "Like the macOS presets I mentioned earlier, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=222"
  },
  {
    "text": "Reference Mode uses color management ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=224"
  },
  {
    "text": "to support several different media formats.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=226"
  },
  {
    "text": "This ensures that color is rendered accurately ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=229"
  },
  {
    "text": "based on the specification for each format.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=231"
  },
  {
    "text": "Of course, to determine how colors should be rendered, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=234"
  },
  {
    "text": "media needs to be tagged to indicate which format it is.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=237"
  },
  {
    "text": "For reference color management to be valid, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=241"
  },
  {
    "text": "the display should only be viewed ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=243"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the reference environment ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=244"
  },
  {
    "text": "specified by the format standard.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=245"
  },
  {
    "text": "The video format supported by Reference Mode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=248"
  },
  {
    "text": "require a dim environment, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=250"
  },
  {
    "text": "while graphics should be viewed in a bright indoor environment.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=251"
  },
  {
    "text": "So what sort of color management does Reference Mode use? ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=256"
  },
  {
    "text": "All formats of color managed to a similar spec.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=260"
  },
  {
    "text": "This includes a D65 white point and a peak luminance ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=262"
  },
  {
    "text": "of 100 nits for SDR media or 1000 nits for HDR media.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=265"
  },
  {
    "text": "For HDR formats, tone-mapping is disabled so the display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=270"
  },
  {
    "text": "will precisely track the format's transfer function.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=273"
  },
  {
    "text": "And colors will be displayed correctly ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=276"
  },
  {
    "text": "as long as they don't exceed 1000 nits ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=278"
  },
  {
    "text": "and are within the P3 color gamut, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=280"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is the iPad's native gamut.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=282"
  },
  {
    "text": "Colors that are out of gamut or brighter than 1000 nits ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=284"
  },
  {
    "text": "will be clipped with no tone-mapping.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=286"
  },
  {
    "text": "The result of that clipping may vary based on the format.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=288"
  },
  {
    "text": "Speaking of formats, here's a list of the ones ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=293"
  },
  {
    "text": "supported by Reference Mode, along with the corresponding ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=295"
  },
  {
    "text": "macOS reference display preset for each.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=297"
  },
  {
    "text": "On iPad, Reference Mode will determine ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=301"
  },
  {
    "text": "the appropriate color management based on color tagging, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=302"
  },
  {
    "text": "so there's no need to switch between presets.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=305"
  },
  {
    "text": "One example of tagging are the ITU H.273 code points ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=308"
  },
  {
    "text": "included in this table, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=312"
  },
  {
    "text": "which you may know as NCLC color tags from QuickTime.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=313"
  },
  {
    "text": "But there are other forms of tagging that can also be used.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=316"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app uses a format that isn't on this list, don't worry.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=320"
  },
  {
    "text": "Reference Mode still color manages unsupported formats; ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=323"
  },
  {
    "text": "they'll just be rendered in a similar way ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=325"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the default display mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=327"
  },
  {
    "text": "You may notice that some of these rows ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=330"
  },
  {
    "text": "include multiple formats.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=332"
  },
  {
    "text": "That's because the formats listed in the same row should ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=334"
  },
  {
    "text": "result in the same rendering on a reference display.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=336"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, HDR10 and BT.2100 PQ both use ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=340"
  },
  {
    "text": "the BT 2020 color primaries, the PQ transfer function, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=344"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the BT 2020 YCC matrix as described by the code points ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=347"
  },
  {
    "text": "9-16-9.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=352"
  },
  {
    "text": "But HDR10 also includes HDR metadata ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=354"
  },
  {
    "text": "that can be used to inform tone-mapping.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=357"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the iPad's default display mode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=360"
  },
  {
    "text": "this could result in different renditions of the same content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=362"
  },
  {
    "text": "depending on the format.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=364"
  },
  {
    "text": "But since Reference Mode does not tone-map, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=366"
  },
  {
    "text": "any HDR metadata is ignored ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=368"
  },
  {
    "text": "and both formats are rendered identically.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=370"
  },
  {
    "text": "Generally speaking, reference displays are calibrated ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=374"
  },
  {
    "text": "with an optical measurement device to ensure color accuracy.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=377"
  },
  {
    "text": "Like macOS presets, Reference Mode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=380"
  },
  {
    "text": "includes a fine-tuned calibration feature ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=382"
  },
  {
    "text": "that allows the white point chromaticity and luminance ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=385"
  },
  {
    "text": "to be calibrated at a single point.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=388"
  },
  {
    "text": "This color adjustment is intended to account ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=390"
  },
  {
    "text": "for display aging and differences between ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=392"
  },
  {
    "text": "measurement devices so that your iPad's white point ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=394"
  },
  {
    "text": "and peak luminance will match other displays ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=396"
  },
  {
    "text": "that have been calibrated with the same device.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=399"
  },
  {
    "text": "That wraps up the specifics of Reference Mode's capabilities ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=402"
  },
  {
    "text": "in color rendering.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=404"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, let's discuss the UIScreen APIs ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=406"
  },
  {
    "text": "associated with Reference Mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=409"
  },
  {
    "text": "But before doing so, I should quickly recap what EDR is.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=411"
  },
  {
    "text": "EDR stands for extended dynamic range ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=416"
  },
  {
    "text": "and is Apple's HDR technology.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=419"
  },
  {
    "text": "It includes both rendering technologies ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=421"
  },
  {
    "text": "and pixel representations.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=423"
  },
  {
    "text": "EDR pixels can represent both SDR and HDR content.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=425"
  },
  {
    "text": "An important component of EDR is headroom, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=429"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is the HDR peak luminance ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=431"
  },
  {
    "text": "divided by the SDR peak luminance.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=433"
  },
  {
    "text": "In Reference Mode, HDR peak is always 1000 nits ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=436"
  },
  {
    "text": "and SDR peak is always 100 nits, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=439"
  },
  {
    "text": "meaning EDR headroom is always 10 times.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=441"
  },
  {
    "text": "EDR ensures that SDR pixels, which are represented ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=446"
  },
  {
    "text": "with values from zero to one, are always rendered.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=449"
  },
  {
    "text": "Any values between one and the EDR headroom ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=452"
  },
  {
    "text": "will be properly rendered without tone-mapping, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=454"
  },
  {
    "text": "while values that are brighter than EDR headroom ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=457"
  },
  {
    "text": "will be clipped.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=459"
  },
  {
    "text": "However, there may be cases where you decide ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=461"
  },
  {
    "text": "that the headroom is not high enough to justify rendering ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=463"
  },
  {
    "text": "your content as EDR and instead want to implement an SDR path.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=465"
  },
  {
    "text": "There may also be times when you prefer to make use ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=470"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the available EDR headroom by applying your own tone-mapping.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=472"
  },
  {
    "text": "In either case, UIScreen has new query properties ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=476"
  },
  {
    "text": "and notifications you can use to make rendering decisions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=479"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=482"
  },
  {
    "text": "More specifically, you can use UIScreen to register ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=484"
  },
  {
    "text": "for notifications about changes in Reference Mode status ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=487"
  },
  {
    "text": "and then query for changes in that status.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=490"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can also use UIScreen to query the device's current ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=493"
  },
  {
    "text": "and potential EDR headroom properties.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=496"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll talk more about that a bit later.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=498"
  },
  {
    "text": "For changes in display mode status, register for the ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=501"
  },
  {
    "text": "UIScreen.referenceDisplayMode StatusDidChangeNotification.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=504"
  },
  {
    "text": "For query purposes, you can use this notification ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=510"
  },
  {
    "text": "to get the new status and the new potential EDR headroom, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=512"
  },
  {
    "text": "both of which may inform rendering decisions in your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=515"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, you might want your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=519"
  },
  {
    "text": "to apply its own tone-mapping based on the EDR headroom ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=520"
  },
  {
    "text": "when Reference Mode is disabled ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=523"
  },
  {
    "text": "and not apply any tone-mapping if Reference Mode is enabled.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=524"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once you receive a notification for a change ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=530"
  },
  {
    "text": "in display mode status, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=532"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can use the reference display mode status property ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=533"
  },
  {
    "text": "of UIScreen to get the current status.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=536"
  },
  {
    "text": "This will be one of four enumerated types.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=539"
  },
  {
    "text": "If StatusEnabled is returned, then Reference Mode is enabled ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=542"
  },
  {
    "text": "and is rendering as expected.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=545"
  },
  {
    "text": "If StatusLimited is returned, then Reference Mode is enabled ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=547"
  },
  {
    "text": "but temporarily can't render a reference response ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=550"
  },
  {
    "text": "due to EDR headroom being limited to less than 10 times.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=553"
  },
  {
    "text": "If this status occurs, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=556"
  },
  {
    "text": "a UI notification will also inform your users ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=558"
  },
  {
    "text": "that the reference rendering is compromised.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=560"
  },
  {
    "text": "If StatusNotEnabled is returned, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=563"
  },
  {
    "text": "then Reference Mode is supported on this device, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=565"
  },
  {
    "text": "but it hasn't been enabled by the user.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=567"
  },
  {
    "text": "And lastly, if StatusNotSupported is returned, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=570"
  },
  {
    "text": "then Reference Mode is not supported on this device.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=573"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, let's take a look at some Swift code to see ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=577"
  },
  {
    "text": "how you can take advantage of UIScreen notifications.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=579"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here, we'll start by getting a default notification object ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=583"
  },
  {
    "text": "from the NotificationCenter.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=586"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then, we'll add a notification observer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=588"
  },
  {
    "text": "to your default notification object.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=590"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this example, the screenChangedEvent selector ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=592"
  },
  {
    "text": "determines the message that the receiver sends to the observer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=595"
  },
  {
    "text": "to alert the observer that the notification is posted.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=598"
  },
  {
    "text": "The name of the notification to register ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=602"
  },
  {
    "text": "for delivery to the observer is ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=603"
  },
  {
    "text": "UIScreen.referenceDisplayMode StatusDidChangeNotification.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=605"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now whenever the status changes, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=611"
  },
  {
    "text": "the function screenChangedEvent will be called.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=613"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this example implementation of screenChangedEvent, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=617"
  },
  {
    "text": "we'll first get a UIScreen from the window scene.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=620"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then, we can get the new referenceDisplayModeStatus ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=624"
  },
  {
    "text": "property from the UIScreen.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=626"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can also get the new potential EDR headroom value ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=629"
  },
  {
    "text": "and use it in your application's rendering paths.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=632"
  },
  {
    "text": "That covers Reference Mode status-change notifications, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=635"
  },
  {
    "text": "so let's move on to talking about EDR headroom.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=638"
  },
  {
    "text": "Earlier, I mentioned two types of EDR headroom: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=642"
  },
  {
    "text": "current and potential.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=645"
  },
  {
    "text": "These properties are relevant to any developer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=646"
  },
  {
    "text": "working with EDR and are not specific to Reference Mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=648"
  },
  {
    "text": "Potential headroom returns the maximum possible headroom ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=651"
  },
  {
    "text": "of your display.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=654"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, you may decide to use an SDR rendering path ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=655"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your app if potential headroom doesn't exceed 1.0 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=658"
  },
  {
    "text": "or some other threshold.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=661"
  },
  {
    "text": "The current headroom is dynamic and may be less ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=663"
  },
  {
    "text": "than the potential headroom for a variety of reasons.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=665"
  },
  {
    "text": "You may choose to apply tone-mapping in your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=668"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that your content won't exceed the current headroom, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=670"
  },
  {
    "text": "which would cause it to clip.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=672"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's take a look at a simple example.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=674"
  },
  {
    "text": "As in the previous example, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=677"
  },
  {
    "text": "we'll start by getting a UIScreen from windowScene.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=678"
  },
  {
    "text": "From there, we'll get the potential EDR headroom property.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=682"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then we can compare the potential EDR headroom value ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=686"
  },
  {
    "text": "to a threshold and decide whether to implement ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=688"
  },
  {
    "text": "an SDR rendering path or image processing path.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=691"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here is an example of how to use the current EDR headroom ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=694"
  },
  {
    "text": "property of UIScreen.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=697"
  },
  {
    "text": "In a draw call, we can again get a UIScreen from windowScene ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=699"
  },
  {
    "text": "and then grab the UIScreen property currentEDRHeadroom.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=703"
  },
  {
    "text": "You could use this value ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=707"
  },
  {
    "text": "to determine an appropriate tone map ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=708"
  },
  {
    "text": "that will avoid clipping and apply it in your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=709"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now that I've covered UIScreen APIs ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=713"
  },
  {
    "text": "and reviewed some code snippets, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=715"
  },
  {
    "text": "we've reached the end of this video.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=717"
  },
  {
    "text": "To recap, we learned how and when ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=719"
  },
  {
    "text": "to enable Reference Mode on iPad.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=721"
  },
  {
    "text": "We discussed reference color rendering ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=725"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the specific capabilities of Reference Mode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=726"
  },
  {
    "text": "including which media formats it supports.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=728"
  },
  {
    "text": "And finally, we learned about ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=732"
  },
  {
    "text": "UIScreen Reference Mode notifications ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=733"
  },
  {
    "text": "and new properties for querying EDR headroom.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=735"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you want to learn more about EDR and color technology ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=738"
  },
  {
    "text": "on Apple platforms, here's a list of videos ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=741"
  },
  {
    "text": "on related topics from the last few WWDCs.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=743"
  },
  {
    "text": "The \"Explore EDR on iOS\" video from this year ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=748"
  },
  {
    "text": "is especially relevant if you're working with EDR on iPad, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=750"
  },
  {
    "text": "either with or without Reference Mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=753"
  },
  {
    "text": "And that brings us to the end of our talk.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=757"
  },
  {
    "text": "I hope that you'll take advantage of Reference Mode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=760"
  },
  {
    "text": "and its APIs in your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=762"
  },
  {
    "text": "Thanks for watching.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-110337/?time=764"
  }
]